  "local_port": 46786,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at On Assignment?",
  "response": "Starting a new job at On Assignment (now known as Actalent) or any company can be both exciting and nerve-wracking. Here are some key things new employees should keep in mind for their first day:\n\n### 1. **Understand the Company Culture**\n   - **Collaboration:** On Assignment/Actalent emphasizes teamwork and collaboration. Be prepared to work closely with colleagues and build strong professional relationships.\n   - **Professionalism:** The company values professionalism in all interactions, whether with clients, candidates, or team members.\n   - **Adaptability:** Being open to change and willing to take on new challenges is highly regarded.\n\n### 2. **Know the Core Business**\n   - **Staffing and Consulting:** The company specializes in providing staffing and consulting services in engineering, sciences, and other professional fields. Familiarize yourself with the industries they serve.\n   - **Client-Centric:** On Assignment/Actalent is client-focused, so understanding clients\u2019 needs and delivering quality service is essential.\n\n### 3. **Prepare for Training and Onboarding**\n   - **Comprehensive Training:** Expect a structured onboarding process that includes training on tools, processes, and company expectations.\n   - **Ask Questions:** Don\u2019t hesitate to ask questions during training\u2014it\u2019s the best way to learn and show your engagement.\n\n### 4. **Dress Code and Etiquette**\n   - **Business Casual:** The dress code is typically business casual, but it\u2019s always safe to confirm with your manager or HR beforehand.\n   - **Punctuality:** Arrive on time or slightly early to make a good first impression.\n\n### 5. **Technology and Tools**\n   - **Laptops/Devices:** You\u2019ll likely have company-provided equipment. Make sure you\u2019re comfortable with the tools and software you\u2019ll be using.\n   - **Communication Platforms:** Familiarize yourself with communication tools like email, Microsoft Teams, or Slack, as these are commonly used for internal and external communication.\n\n### 6. **Performance Expectations**\n   - **Metrics-Driven:** The company often sets clear performance metrics, so be prepared to track and meet your goals.\n   - **Proactive Approach:** Taking initiative and being proactive in your role will help you stand out.\n\n### 7. **Networking and Relationship Building**\n   - **Internal Networking:** Take the time to introduce yourself to colleagues and build relationships across teams.\n   - **External Networking:** If your role involves interacting with clients or candidates, focus on building trust and rapport.\n\n### 8. **Company Policies and Benefits**\n   - **HR Policies:** Review the employee handbook to understand company policies, including time off, remote work, and professional development opportunities.\n   - **Benefits:** Familiarize yourself with the benefits package, including health insurance, retirement plans, and any other perks.\n\n### 9. **Set Goals and Communicate**\n   - **Short-Term Goals:** Identify what you want to achieve in your first 30, 60, and 90 days.\n   - **Open Communication:** Maintain open lines of communication with your manager to ensure alignment on expectations.\n\n### 10. **Stay Positive and Patient**\n   - **Learning Curve:** There will be a lot to absorb in the beginning, so be patient with yourself as you learn.\n   - **Positive Attitude:** Show enthusiasm and a willingness to contribute, which will leave a lasting impression.\n\nBy keeping these points in mind, you\u2019ll set yourself up for a successful and smooth start at On Assignment/Actalent. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
